<TopicLayout slug="hell">
  <p class="lede"><b>"A picture is worth a thousand words"</b></p>
  <p>
    And yet the one above still manages to fall short of the gravity of the eternal agony of damnation.
  </p>

  <p class="lede">
    <b>Take a closer look at our topic, but by all means avoid it being your destiny.</b>
  </p>

  <div class="bubble2 hell-bubble">
    <p>
      <b>John 3:16</b><br />
      &ldquo;For God so loved the world that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him shall not
      perish but have eternal life.&rdquo;
    </p>

    <p>
      This verse speaks of love and hope for humanity, but it also reveals the reason for the dire need of love
      and hope for humanity.
    </p>
    <p>
      The verse implies that whoever does not believe in Jesus Christ, the Son of God, will perish and have
      eternal death.
    </p>
    <p class="interlude">
      The implication is true.<br />
      The reality horrifying.
    </p>
    <p>The infamous name for this horrifying reality, this "living" eternal death is Hell.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>DO YOU QUALIFY FOR HELL?</h2>

  <div class="bubble2 hell-bubble">
    <p>
      <b>2 Thessalonians 2:10</b><br />
      &ldquo;and all the ways that wickedness deceives those who are perishing. They perish because they refused
      to love the truth and so be saved.&rdquo;
    </p>

    <p>If you refuse to love the truth you qualify for hell. Jesus is the Truth(John 14:6)</p>
    <p>
      Wickedness is deceitful.<br />
      That lust, that greed, that pride, that temporary pleasure, it's deceiving you; like the Pied Piper with
      his merry tune, it's luring you to destruction.
    </p>

    <p class="interlude">
      "The safest road to Hell is the graduation one - the gentle slope, soft underfoot, without sudden
      turnings, without milestones, without sign posts." C.S. Lewis
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>Hebrews 10:26-27</b><br />
      &ldquo;If we deliberately keep on sinning after we have received the knowledge of the truth, no sacrifice
      for sins is left, but only a fearful expectation of judgment and of raging fire that will consume the
      enemies of God.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Matthew 13:40-42</b><br />
      &ldquo;As the weeds are pulled up and burned in the fire, so it will be at the end of the age. The Son of Man
      will send out his angels, and they will weed out of his kingdom everything that causes sin and all who
      do evil. They will throw them into the blazing furnace, where there will be weeping and gnashing of
      teeth.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Jesus says this of Hell: Mark 9:48</b><br />
      &ldquo;where &lsquo;the worms that eat them do not die, and the fire is not quenched.&rsquo;&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Psalm 11:6-7</b><br />
      &ldquo;On the wicked he will rain fiery coals and burning sulfur; a scorching wind will be their lot. For the
      Lord is righteous, he loves justice; the upright will see his face.&rdquo;
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="interlude">
    To be a resident of Hell: is to be "utterly alone, in the darkness without a single comfort or
    consolation, nothing good, without hope for all eternity."<br />
    - Kaylene R
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>2 Thessalonians 1:8-9</b><br />
      &ldquo;He will punish those who do not know God and do not obey the gospel of our Lord Jesus. They will be
      punished with everlasting destruction and shut out from the presence of the Lord and from the glory of
      his might&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Matthew 10:28</b><br />
      &ldquo;Do not be afraid of those who kill the body but cannot kill the soul. Rather, be afraid of the One who
      can destroy both soul and body in hell.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Isaiah 14:9-11</b><br />
      &ldquo;The realm of the dead below is all astir to meet you at your coming; it rouses the spirits of the
      departed to greet you&mdash;all those who were leaders in the world; it makes them rise from their
      thrones&mdash;all those who were kings over the nations. They will all respond, they will say to you,
      &lsquo;You also have become weak, as we are; you have become like us.&rsquo; All your pomp has been brought down
      to the grave, along with the noise of your harps; maggots are spread out beneath you and worms cover
      you.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>2 Peter 3:7</b><br />
      &ldquo;By the same word the present heavens and earth are reserved for fire, being kept for the day of
      judgment and destruction of the ungodly.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Revelation 14:10-11</b><br />
      &ldquo;they, too, will drink the wine of God&rsquo;s fury, which has been poured full strength into the cup of his
      wrath. They will be tormented with burning sulfur in the presence of the holy angels and of the Lamb.
      And the smoke of their torment will rise for ever and ever. There will be no rest day or night for those
      who worship the beast and its image, or for anyone who receives the mark of its name.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Matthew 25:41, 46</b><br />
      &ldquo;Then he will say to those on his left, &lsquo;Depart from me, you who are cursed, into the eternal fire
      prepared for the devil and his angels.&rsquo;&rdquo;<br /><br />
      &ldquo;Then they will go away to eternal punishment, but the righteous to eternal life.&rdquo;
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>WHO DESERVES SUCH A SEVERE JUDGMENT?</h2>

  <p class="lede"><b>You. I. Everyone.</b></p>
  <p>
    If you don't agree with this being a justified condemnation, you are not aware of the height of the
    purity of God, nor the depth of your own depravity.
  </p>
  <p>We are in the realm of humans.</p>
  <p>God is in the realm of God.</p>
  <p>What would make us think that we are even capable of earning a spot in His Presence?</p>

  <p class="interlude">
    "Morality may keep you out of jail, but it takes the blood of Jesus to keep you out of hell."<br />
    - Charles Spurgeon
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>Matthew 16:24-26</b><br />
      &ldquo;Then Jesus said to his disciples, &lsquo;Whoever wants to be my disciple must deny themselves and take up
      their cross and follow me. For whoever wants to save their life will lose it, but whoever loses their
      life for me will find it. What good will it be for someone to gain the whole world, yet forfeit their
      soul? Or what can anyone give in exchange for their soul?&rsquo;&rdquo;
    </li>
  </ul>

